# Commit SHAs whose changes should be ignored by `git blame`.
#
# These are typically bulk reformat or rename passes that shift every line
# without changing program behaviour. Including them here keeps blame output
# focused on the commits that actually authored each line.
#
# Convention: one full-length commit SHA per line. An optional `# comment`
# trailer is allowed for context (the commit subject, e.g. the PR number, or
# the rule that drove the rewrite).
#
# Configure git to consult this file by default:
#
#     git config blame.ignoreRevsFile .git-blame-ignore-revs
#
# (or pass `--ignore-revs-file=.git-blame-ignore-revs` ad-hoc).
#
# Phase A of the Ruff + pre-commit adoption deliberately does not run
# `ruff format`; Phase B will append the bulk-reformat merge-commit SHA
# below.
